name: Rolex Daytona
description: The Rolex Cosmograph Daytona is a mechanical chronograph wristwatch designed to meet the needs of racing drivers by measuring elapsed time and calculating average speed

name: Patek Philippe
description: Switzerland has become synonymous with luxury watches and one of the top Swiss watch brands of all time is Patek Philippe

name: Audemars Piguet
description: Audemars Piguet is one of the most famous high-end watch companies in the world

name: A.Lange & Söhne
description: The first German luxury watch brand on our list, at A. Lange and Söhne, excellence and perfection is a priority at every stage of the process.

name: Omega
description: Omega watches have travelled to the North Pole, been launched into space, and descended into the depths of the ocean in submarines.

name: Blancpain
description: Perpetual calendars, tourbillons, carousels, and chronographs—the level of intricacy of the mechanisms contained within a Blancpain watch are astounding.

name: IWC Schaffhausen
description: An IWC Schaffhausen watch is that rare thing: a luxury accessory that marries flawless functionality with exceptional design.

name: Jaeger-LeCoultre
description: Jaeger-LeCoultre is known within the industry for its inventiveness.With its legendary rectangular design, it’s a horological great—and the perfect unisex watch.

name: Chopard
description: Known for its contemporary and playful designs, Chopard offers a fashionable and creative timepiece for style-savvy shoppers.

name: Y-Piaget
description: Piaget is most famous for being a pioneer in ultra-thin watch calibers. This is the company behind both the world’s thinnest manual wind watch and the world’s thinnest automatic watch.

name: Cartier
description: Cartier’s range of luxury watches are some of the most celebrated timepieces on the market and the brand has established itself as a major player within the watch-making industry

name: Vacheron Constantin
description: Vacheron Constantin is the most established luxury watch brand on this list—and the world’s oldest continuously operating watch-maker.
